The paper discusses a computer security technique (CFI) and evaluates the security policies enforced by 21 recent hardware-based CFI architectures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the practicality, hardware cost, and performance of these architectures, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
